    featuredImagePrompt: "A conceptual visual depicting the 14th Amendment to the US Constitution as a weathered, ancient scroll, with a modern gavel poised above it, suggesting legal challenge and reinterpretation. Behind it, subtle abstract outlines of the United States map and diverse human figures, symbolizing the population and the foundational nature of citizenship. The color palette should be serious and judicial, with deep blues, muted golds, and parchment tones, conveying the gravity of the constitutional debate. The composition should be dynamic, showing tension and the fragility of the document under scrutiny.",
