      bearCase: "The hawkish Federal Reserve\'s \'higher-for-longer\' interest rate policy, clearly signaled by the bond market, will continue to make fixed-income assets more attractive than non-yielding Bitcoin. Failure to breach $61,775, coupled with a breach of $59,100, could lead to further price declines. Ongoing regulatory crackdowns and a lack of Bitcoin leadership against altcoins also contribute to a bearish outlook.",
