      bearCase: "Despite the hype, SpaceX faces immense execution risks with its ambitious projects, particularly Starship and the continuous expansion of Starlink. The valuation implied by the $75 billion IPO could be considered aggressive, especially if the \'AI bubble\' narrative gains traction. High capital intensity, intense competition, and regulatory uncertainties could weigh on profitability and long-term shareholder returns. Over-reliance on Elon Musk and potential geopolitical disruptions also pose significant risks to the company\'s trajectory.",
