      bearCase: "The bear case suggests that escalating Iran-U.S. tensions, coupled with a hawkish surprise from the Fed or ambiguous \'Fedspeak,\' could trigger a broader market correction. Further profit warnings from multinational corporations, particularly those exposed to geopolitical hotspots or slowing economies like China, could dampen investor sentiment. A significant unwinding of the AI trade, perhaps due to valuation concerns, could also lead to a sharp decline in tech-heavy indices.",
      neutralCase: "A neutral outlook anticipates continued choppiness and a bifurcated market. The S&P 500 may remain range-bound, oscillating between record highs and significant pullbacks, reflecting a balance of bullish growth drivers and bearish geopolitical/monetary risks. The Dow could continue to outperform due to its defensive characteristics, while the Nasdaq might experience periods of both strong gains and corrections as the AI trade matures and valuations are scrutinized. No major breakout or breakdown is expected in the near term, but rather a period of consolidation and re-evaluation.",
      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "Our probability-weighted outlook assigns a 40% chance of a neutral market, characterized by ongoing volatility and mixed performance across indices, largely due to conflicting macro signals. There\'s a 35% chance of a modestly bullish scenario if Fed communication is clear and geopolitical risks remain contained, leading to selective gains. A 25% chance of a bearish downturn exists if geopolitical tensions escalate significantly or the Fed delivers an unexpectedly hawkish message.",
