    keyHighlights: ["10 SMEs file draft papers with SEBI in May, up 25% from April", "Subscription rates for recent SME IPOs have been strong, with some issues oversubscribed by over 100 times", "Investor appetite for SME IPOs remains high, driven by attractive valuations and growth potential", "SME IPOs have raised over Rs 1,500 crore in the first five months of 2026, a 50% increase from the same period last year", "SEBI\'s relaxed norms for SME IPOs have contributed to the increase in filings and investor interest"],
    executiveSummary: "The Indian SME IPO market is experiencing a surge in activity, with 10 companies filing draft papers in May alone. This increase in filings, combined with strong subscription rates for recent SME IPOs, indicates a strong investor appetite for smaller issues. According to market experts, the attractive valuations and growth potential of SMEs are driving investor interest.",
    marketBackground: "The Indian IPO market has been performing well in 2026, with several mainboard and SME IPOs receiving strong investor response. The SME IPO market, in particular, has seen a significant increase in activity, with 10 companies filing draft papers in May alone. This increase in filings is expected to continue, driven by SEBI\'s relaxed norms for SME IPOs and the attractive valuations of smaller companies.",
    detailedAnalysis: "## Market Overview\nThe Indian SME IPO market is witnessing a significant uptick in activity, with 10 companies filing draft papers in May alone. This increase in filings is driven by SEBI\'s relaxed norms for SME IPOs, which have made it easier for smaller companies to raise capital from the public markets.\n## Key Developments\nThe recent SME IPOs have seen strong subscription rates, with some issues oversubscribed by over 100 times. This indicates a strong investor appetite for SME IPOs, driven by attractive valuations and growth potential. According to market experts, the SME IPO market is expected to continue to see strong activity in the coming months.\n## Market Impact\nThe surge in SME IPO activity is expected to have a positive impact on the Indian capital markets, providing smaller companies with access to capital and creating new investment opportunities for investors. According to Rohan Patel, an analyst at a leading brokerage firm, \'The SME IPO market is an important platform for smaller companies to raise capital and grow their businesses. The strong investor appetite for SME IPOs is a positive sign for the Indian capital markets.\'\n## Expert Perspective\nThe strong investor appetite for SME IPOs is driven by the attractive valuations and growth potential of smaller companies. According to market experts, the SME IPO market is expected to continue to see strong activity in the coming months, driven by the relaxed norms and the strong investor appetite.\n## Historical Context\nThe Indian SME IPO market has seen significant growth in recent years, driven by the relaxed norms and the strong investor appetite. In 2025, the SME IPO market saw a record number of filings, with over 100 companies raising capital from the public markets.\n---\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\nPublished by PulseTrends",
